snippet.textDisplay: This would have been a good song except that it doesn't fit in with coke studio at all. Coke studio is supposed to be about fusion experimentation. This is hardly that. This is nothing more than a Hindi song put to Western instruments. That in and of itself isn't fusion. Moreover, this has the look and feel of a bollywood production to it. The overly animated musicians and the way it's filmed. This is exactly how the first season started (except way more shittier) and it tanked. Why does everything in India have to look like a fuckin bollywood production? Be original for God's sake. You guys have a culture and history that's more than a thousand years old and yet everything revolves around your third rate movie industry. Quit trying to be Western. You're anything but western.
